// Semantic direction:
// kompileringstids_beregning runs Norscode code during compilation, producing zero-cost constants.
// ktb_budsjett prevents runaway compile-time execution by capping instruction steps and memory.
// konst_funksjon is a regular function with the `konst` qualifier that the evaluator can execute at compile time.
// konst_fn_rekursjon is allowed but must terminate; the evaluator tracks rekursjons_dybde.
// kompileringstid_assert causes a compile error if the constant expression evaluates to false.
// kompileringstid_size_of returns the byte size of a type as a compile-time constant.
// konst_generikk allows type parameters to carry value arguments — like Rust's `const N: usize`.
// avhengig_array_lengde makes [T; N] where N is a konst_parameter statically checked.
// array_av_n generates arrays whose length is a type-level natural number.
// bitflagg_av_n creates a bitmask integer type sized to exactly N bits.
// tabell_generer populates a lookup table at compile time, e.g. sinus_tabell[i] = sin(i*π/256).
// crc_tabell precomputes all 256 CRC polynomial remainders for fast runtime CRC-32 computation.
// type_nat is the type-level Peano natural number (type_null_nat = 0, type_succ wraps).
// type_vektor is a length-indexed list: type_vektor(T, N) has exactly N elements.
// zip_med_bevis zips two type_vektorer only if they have the same length — enforced by the type system.
// infinite_loop_guard detects non-terminating konst loops and emits a compile error.

// Primitive flow:
// konst tabell: konst SIN_TABELL: [Desimal; 256] = generer_sinus_tabell()
//   kompilator kjører generer_sinus_tabell() ved kompileringstid
//   -> bakes inn som data-seksjon i binæret, null runtime-kostnad
// konst_generikk: fn nullstilt_array<konst N: Usize>() -> [Heltall; N]
//   kall: nullstilt_array::<8>() -> type-sjekker verifiserer N=8 -> genererer array på stack
// type_vektor: fn head<T, konst N: Usize>(v: Vektor<T, N+1>) -> T
//   -> kan ikke kalle head på tom vektor: N+1 ≥ 1 alltid sant
// kompileringstid_assert: kompileringstid_assert!(størrelse_av::<Hode>() == 24)
//   -> kompileringsfeil hvis struct-størrelse endres uventet

// This defines compile-time computation: const functions with recursion budgets, const generics
// for length-indexed arrays and bitmasks, lookup table precomputation, type-level natural numbers
// with length-indexed vectors, and compile-time assertions for layout invariants.
